{"parse":{"title":"Bharti Foundation","pageid":35059164,"revid":724159259,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption class=\"fn org\">Bharti Foundation</caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Bharti_logo.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Bharti logo.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e9/Bharti_logo.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"141\" data-file-width=\"161\" data-file-height=\"91\" /></a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Satyabharti.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Satyabharti.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Satyabharti.jpg/220px-Satyabharti.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"124\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Satyabharti.jpg/330px-Satyabharti.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Satyabharti.jpg/440px-Satyabharti.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2592\" data-file-height=\"1456\" /></a><div>Satya Bharti School run by Bharti Foundation</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Founded</th><td class=\"note\">\n2000</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Founder</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Sunil_Mittal\" title=\"Sunil Mittal\">Sunil Mittal</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Type</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Private_foundation\" title=\"Private foundation\">Non-government private foundation</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Focus</th><td>\nTo improve the accessibility and quality of education at school level across rural India</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Location</th><td class=\"label\">\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Airtel Center, <a href=\"/wiki/Gurgaon\" title=\"Gurgaon\">Gurgaon</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Area served </div></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/India\" title=\"India\">India</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Method</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Public-private_partnership\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Public-private partnership\">Public-private partnership</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Owner</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Bharti_Enterprises\" title=\"Bharti Enterprises\">Bharti Enterprises</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Key people</div></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Sunil_Mittal\" title=\"Sunil Mittal\">Sunil Mittal</a> (Chairman)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Website</th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.bhartifoundation.org\">bhartifoundation.org</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Bharti Foundation</b> is the philanthropic arm of <a href=\"/wiki/Bharti_Enterprises\" title=\"Bharti Enterprises\">Bharti Enterprises</a>, an <a href=\"/wiki/India\" title=\"India\">Indian</a> business <a href=\"/wiki/Conglomerate_(company)\" title=\"Conglomerate (company)\">conglomerate</a> based in <a href=\"/wiki/New_Delhi\" title=\"New Delhi\">New Delhi</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It conducts free programs in both primary and <a href=\"/wiki/Higher_education\" title=\"Higher education\">higher education</a> for the underprivileged children, with a particular focus on girls. The Satya Bharti School Program, started in 2006, is the flagship program of Bharti Foundation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The foundation, based in <a href=\"/wiki/Gurgaon\" title=\"Gurgaon\">Gurgaon</a>, India, is governed by 16 board members, including <a href=\"/wiki/Sunil_Mittal\" title=\"Sunil Mittal\">Sunil Mittal</a> as its chairman and Rakesh Mittal as its co-chairman.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The foundation has been recognized by many societies and award committees for its <a href=\"/wiki/Corporate_social_responsibility\" title=\"Corporate social responsibility\">corporate social responsibility</a> programs. Some of them include the Global CSR Award, Asian CSR Award, The Indian Education Award 2011, and World Education Award 2011.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bharti_Foundation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.bhartifoundation.org/wps/wcm/connect/bhartifoundation/BhartiFoundation/Home\">\"About Us\"</a>. <i>Bharti Foundation</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">14 March</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Bharti+Foundation&amp;rft.atitle=About+Us&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhartifoundation.org%2Fwps%2Fwcm%2Fconnect%2Fbhartifoundation%2FBhartiFoundation%2FHome&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABharti+Foundation\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <s